Title: Python Developer
Job_Description:
The Python Developer role entails responsibilities within our python infrastructure spanning a number of domains—from data engineering to workflow development—with a focus on data-driven middle tier development. As an integral member of the team, you will collaborate closely with other engineers and researchers to identify requirements and build robust internal tools.

· Transforming and cleaning data retrieved by API end points
· Working with research and technology teams to provide production support for signal dashboards and processes

The primary role of the Technical Scholar will be in guiding our resellers through the TD SYNNEX ecosystem while providing presales design consultation. They will need to understand current technologies including cloud, security, data center, and networking in order to provide product recommendations, create Bill of Materials, scope projects, and provide licensing information on products not supported by the existing Pre-Sales Sales Engineering team. TD Description
Tell us your story. Don't go unnoticed. Explain why you're a winning candidate. Think "TD" if you crave meaningful work and embrace change like we do. We are a trusted North American leader that cares about people and inspires them to grow and move forward.
Stay current and competitive. Carve out a career for yourself. Grow with us. Here's our story: jobs.td.com
Department Overview
What is NEW?

Want to make an impact on your career and others? Join us as we make strategic investments in our people.

Our vision to be the Better Bank is grounded in our purpose-driven and forward-focused strategy. Amidst a rapidly changing landscape, we know that technology plays a critical role in achieving this vision and delivering on our strategy. It also signals the need to accelerate investment in emerging capabilities to adapt to the changes happening around us and respond to customer needs more quickly. To accomplish this, we're evolving our platforms, introducing key enterprise practices and re-imagining our customer journeys as part of the Next Evolution of Work (NEW).

NEW will to make decisions faster, work more efficiently and quickly identify and address customer and market trends to deliver innovative solutions at an unprecedented pace. NEW will enable us to move with purpose towards common goals, how we work and elevate how we deliver . Having the opportunity to contribute and be a part of one of the largest transformation projects at TD is a unique and critical career experience. NEW provides TD's business with better ways to collaborate, deliver and manage solutions for our customers

Roles within the NEW model are similar to roles in external organizations – it's the way the future of work is heading – in leading global organizations and beyond; you're developing highly marketable skills that TD and industry leaders are seeking. By joining NEW, you'll have the opportunity to be part of a new way of working while making an impact on the future of banking in ways you've never imagined.


By joining the , you'll drive the continuous development and upskilling of its members, as your leadership will result in talent excellence and delivery success across the Enterprise.

Integral to the success of our business, the playsa critical role. The will define the strategy and roadmap to improve and expand upon our team's capabilities and skillsets within the mobile engineering practice. You're eager to explore new technologies and advise our team on industry best practices. All members of the growing mobile team will seek your wisdom, advice, and mentorship.
Together with its people management and development of the Practice, this role will encourage you to create a community with TD Bank, aligning to a common vision and expanding the knowledge set across the organization by fostering a work culture that encourages productivity, innovation, process improvement, teamwork and a high level of professionalism. It drives change through positive reinforcement of milestones and successes. It creates an environment where the team freely escalates business challenges.

Title: Manager, IT Product Management
Job_Description:
Your Opportunity

The primary responsibility for this role is to ensuring the seamless, uninterrupted operation of our streaming trading platforms and associated admin applications including thinkorswim, TOS Mobile, TOS Web, and all other related Trader Group Applications. This individual proactively monitors all systems for potential issues and as issues occur, will serve as the central point for remediation and resolution. This role will also support Trader Web related activities such as Futures/FX OLA, TD Direct Investing Support, Portfolio Margin OLA and TraderWise/Autotrade related functionality. This role also includes assistance with product development initiatives at all stages of the product development life cycle as well as tackling additional applications in a support role.

We're proud to support our employees in a working approach that allows you to bring your best self to work – whether that’s in the office or remote.

Title: Program Director (EPMO, Remote)
Job_Description:
Overview

As a Project Manager you will critically evaluate information gathered from multiple sources, reconcile conflicts, decompose high-level information into details, abstract up from low-level information to a general understanding, and distinguish user requests from the underlying true needs. A key part of providing transparency is governance; you will assist in the overall management and governance of the program/assigned work stream(s) including producing status, scorecards, and other key program management elements.

We are looking for someone that is eager to learn the ins-and-outs of the business transformation process and leverage the project management methodologies for project success. This individual most be is willing to roll up their sleeves and learn to act as a player-coach. It's critical that the Project Manager bring enthusiasm and inquisitiveness to the job every day.

The purpose of this position is to drive process redesign through identifying areas needing improvement, collaborating with the proper stakeholders and influencing the team to define a solution. This position will help value and process map the end to end solution and help the team identify upstream and downstream impacts to the solution. This position will then ensure a project plan is defined, track status and keep the team on track to complete tasks identified in the project plan. They will help identify barriers and either remove them or escalate them. This position will provide status updates on both individual and overall project progress to management and potentially executives.

Title: Risk Management Specialist
Job_Description:
Job Description Summary:

The Cyber Risk Management Specialist is responsible for assessing and managing risk and compliance for the informational and system assets of TD SYNNEX and its suppliers. Will be responsible for leading the implementation of the organization-wide ISMS risk management function of the information security program to ensure information security risks are identified, assessed and monitored. Will be responsible for assessing 3rd party risks of SaaS, IaaS and PaaS partners utilized by the global enterprise. Will be responsible for providing assurances to reseller, vendor partners and other organizations that seek attestations from TD SYNNEX on it's security program. Responsibilities also include teaching and mentoring junior staff members to learn and apply industry best practices for risk management.

The purpose of this position is to provide front line leadership and domain expertise for implementation of the GRC management program. Responsibilities require leadership and project management; experience, as well as expertise to ensure effective system-wide security analysis; standards and testing; risk assessment; development of policies, standards and guidelines.

About TD Bank, America's Most Convenient Bank®
TD Bank, America's Most Convenient Bank, is one of the 10 largest banks in the U.S., providing more than 8 million customers with a full range of retail, small business and commercial banking products and services at approximately 1,300 convenient locations throughout the Northeast, Mid-Atlantic, Metro D.C., the Carolinas and Florida. In addition, TD Bank and its subsidiaries offer customized private banking and wealth management services through TD Wealth®, and vehicle financing and dealer commercial services through TD Auto Finance. TD Bank is headquartered in Cherry Hill, N.J.
TD Bank, America's Most Convenient Bank, is a member of TD Bank Group and a subsidiary of The Toronto-Dominion Bank of Toronto, Canada, a top 10 financial services company in North America. The Toronto-Dominion Bank trades on the New York and Toronto stock exchanges under the ticker symbol "TD".

Title: Business Analyst I (US)
Job_Description:
Summary:

Provides analytical support to a specific functional area or department. Provides regular reporting for assigned area/department.

Assists in the preparation and analysis of ad hoc operational or financial performance reports.

Essential Duties & Responsibilities Required:
Compiles and loads data received from other departments utilizing spreadsheet and database applications 25%
Maintains systems applications, including managing users, profiles, account access, security, and troubleshooting issues 20%
Assists in preparation for management reviews and budgeting activities, as required 15%

Additional Duties required:







Working Conditions:

#LI-CB1

This position is for Shyft Global Services, a leading technology lifecycle service provider that partners with companies around the world to shift the way they do business. Shyft Global Services is a wholly owned subsidiary of TD SYNNEX employing more than 1,500 services professionals and IT experts focused on delivering end-to-end product and customer lifecycle management services for original equipment manufacturers (OEMs) and other technology innovators.

Title: Business Analyst I (US)
Job_Description:
Overview:

As a Data Analyst for our Cloud FinOps team, you'll lead strategic data visualization projects, develop and deliver qualified data to help us make informed business decisions, and have the opportunity to collaborate with stakeholders in key departments to our business.

What You'll Do

Data & Analysis
Manage cloud operations master data, including creation, mining from multiple sources, cleaning and reorganizing, and deletion.
Interpret data sets, find data trends and patterns valuable for diagnostics, predictive analytics efforts, and achieving business objectives.
